    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a directed graph structure with 14 nodes (microservices) and 14 weighted edges (API call volumes). Synthetic data was generated using Poisson distribution (\u03bb=30) to simulate typical API traffic patterns, with intentional clustering around core services (API Gateway \u03bc=38.3, \u03c3=3.5) and exponential decay for peripheral services. The dependency wheel visualization was chosen to emphasize circular connectivity patterns while maintaining Tufte's data-ink ratio through minimal axis markings. Cairo's perceptual principles are applied through: 1) Hue-based color differentiation for immediate service type recognition, 2) Line weight encoding for traffic volume pre-attentive processing, and 3) Radial symmetry for efficient spatial comparison. Statistical anchors include core service traffic (\u03bc=36.8, \u03c3=6.2) versus support services (\u03bc=21.4, \u03c3=8.7), revealing the architectural hub-and-spoke pattern."
